                    <section id="ccant">
                         <img src="~/assets/img/Diet/ccount.png" style="float:left; padding-right: 25px;" width="400" height="400" />
                         <h2 style="color: #fcc454;">Calorie Counting</h2>
                         <p>
                              Counting calories can be an effective way to manage weight and improve overall health. By tracking the number of calories you consume each day, you can better understand your eating habits and make adjustments to meet your goals.

                              To accurately track your calories, you need to have a good understanding of portion sizes and the nutritional content of the foods you eat. Using a food diary or tracking app can help you keep track of what you eat and the number of calories you consume.

                              It's important to remember that not all calories are created equal. Foods that are high in fiber and protein can help keep you feeling full and satisfied, while foods that are high in sugar and fat can be less satiating and lead to overeating.

                              While calorie counting can be a helpful tool, it's important to approach it in a healthy and balanced way. It's important to still focus on consuming a variety of nutrient-dense foods, staying hydrated, and engaging in regular physical activity.

                              It's also important to be mindful of the potential downsides of calorie counting, such as the potential for obsessive or restrictive behavior. It's important to listen to your body's hunger and fullness cues and seek support if you are struggling with disordered eating habits.
                         </p>
                         <hr width="100%" size="3" noshade>
                    </section>

                    <section id="hpdiet">
                         <img src="~/assets/img/Diet/prot.jpg" style="float:right; padding-left: 25px;" width="600" height="600" />
                         <h2 style="color: #fcc454;">High-Protein Diet</h2>
                         <p>
                              High-protein diets are popular for weight loss and building muscle. Protein is an important nutrient that helps build and repair tissues in the body and can also help keep you feeling full and satisfied.

                              The amount of protein you need depends on your age, sex, weight, and activity level. In general, most people need around 0.8 grams of protein per kilogram of body weight per day. However, people who are very active or trying to build muscle may need more.

                              High-protein diets can help with weight loss because they can help reduce hunger and cravings and may also increase the number of calories your body burns through digestion. However, it's important to still focus on consuming a variety of nutrient-dense foods and not rely solely on protein supplements or processed foods.

                              Some high-protein diets, such as the ketogenic diet, can be very low in carbohydrates. While this may lead to weight loss in the short term, it can be difficult to sustain and may also lead to nutrient deficiencies or other health issues.

                              It's also important to consider the source of your protein. Foods like lean meats, fish, eggs, and dairy products are good sources of protein and also provide other important nutrients like vitamins and minerals. Plant-based sources of protein, such as beans, nuts, and seeds, can also be a healthy part of a high-protein diet.

                              It's important to speak with a healthcare professional or registered dietitian before starting a high-protein diet, especially if you have any underlying health conditions or concerns.
                         </p>
                         <hr width="100%" size="3" noshade>
                    </section>

                    <section id="kdiet">
                         <img src="~/assets/img/Diet/kdiet.jpg" style="float:left; padding-right: 25px;" width="500" height="500" />
                         <h2 style="color: #fcc454;">Keto Diet</h2>
                         <p>
                              The Keto Diet is a low-carbohydrate, high-fat diet that is designed to put the body into a metabolic state called ketosis. By restricting carbohydrate intake and increasing fat intake, the body starts to burn fat for energy instead of glucose from carbohydrates. This can lead to weight loss and other health benefits.

                              The Keto Diet typically involves consuming less than 100 grams of carbohydrates per day and getting the majority of calories from fat sources such as meat, dairy products, oils, and nuts. Protein intake is moderate and should be sufficient to maintain muscle mass.

                              While the Keto Diet has been shown to be effective for weight loss and improving certain health markers, it may not be suitable for everyone. People with certain medical conditions or on certain medications may need to avoid this diet, and it is always important to consult with a healthcare professional before starting any new diet or exercise program.
                         </p>
                    </section>
               </section>

